			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Exended Notes(Benefical  spells only nerf)<a name="67066"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 15 04 12:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Extended Notes doesn't say anything about being beneficial only. To quote directly from the game's description: &quot;This ability will increase your song ranges by 10, 15, and 25 percent.&quot; Sounds to me like that should affect everything. 
<br />

<br />
Sionachie's Crescendo, on the other hand, specifically says 'group songs': &quot;This ability provides an even greater extension to the range of group songs. The three ranks of this ability may be trained once each level for levels 63 and above.&quot; Now, group songs is pretty vague, but one rightfully assumes they mean songs that affect your group.
<br />

<br />
To me, it seems like EN should be affecting everything, as it did originally, no doubt. Then along came SC and provided such a boost to PBAE ranges, which they just couldn't have, so they added a global 'Detrimental spells only' limit to the AA focus. Conveniently, they say that EN was originally supposed to affect beneficial only songs, but I would say that is a cheap way of fixing the range extensions in general.
<br />

<br />
On a side note, obviously AE kiting wasn't as unbalancing with extended AE ranges as it was recently, or they were just too lazy to think of an appropriate nerf for the ability as Grumbuk did.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
