				<td colspan="2"><span>Group songs are not AE.  I recognize freely that EN once DID include DoTs as well as group buffs, but Sony has made it abundantly clear that it was NEVER the intention to have EN affect detrimental songs which are, by definition NOT GROUP SONGS.  So you can complain all you want about how they changed it, but the fact is they did NOT break EN -- the FIXED it.  Now you want them to go back and break it again because the fix didn't stop you from doing something they didn't want you to do necessitating even more fixing.  Get over it -- EN isn't supposed to affect AOE.  It never was and what's more -- they never SAID it was.  Not one time have they explicitly said EN should affect detrimental, targeted, or area-effect songs.  They HAVE specifically said group songs - not one of which fits the restriction described in the previous sentence.  To be perfectly objective, if I was an EQ programmer, the last class that would get an extended range focus on targeted affects is the one class that can move while casting and therefore needs it the least.</span></td>
