				<td colspan="2"><span>It has been answered, either in this forum or others.
<br />

<br />
We can cast running.  Our range is technically infinite because of this, you can outrun the mob so it will always be at max range.
<br />

<br />
If you run at say X and mob runs at X-2, this means mob will never catch you, and since you can run and cast you can always keep the mob at maximum range.  There are few mobs that can run faster than a bard (if any).
<br />

<br />
I think the current AA's have been explained plenty and the true intent of them.
<br />

<br />
It would be nice to recieve some of the effects from items but WAIT! instrument mod thats right...
<br />

<br />
The only real issue is the instrument mod cap which is crap just a corner dev's cut to minimize issues they were finding with bards which THEY caused with insufficient planning.  Several instruments so far have put bards past the cap... the fact we have to spend aa's to gain the full effect of our instrument mods is alittle ridiculous.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">So no one has yet answered the question of why we can't have extended range on our songs JUST LIKE OTHER CLASSES GET? </span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />
So basically in response to that:
<br />
We are bards not wizards, enchanters, shamans etc etc.  They get their effects we get ours.</span></td>
